a.\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1418, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999980568646, \"rank\": 1.9001275881520847e-09, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 1586, \"end\": 1591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9381970247967566, \"rank\": 0.06192129563232307, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"full confidence\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1463}, {\"ngram\": \"a well-balanced team\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1518}, {\"ngram\": \"their superior collective difficulty score\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1565}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"D-score\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1578}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Based on simulations of the teams' routines on the six apparatuses, Japan's D-score tally was likely to top China's, according to Mizutori.\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1662, \"end\": 1667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 3.76747469383612e-13, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 1702, \"end\": 1707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9381970247967566, \"rank\": 0.06192129563232307, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"simulations\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1614}, {\"ngram\": \"the teams' routines\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"the six apparatuses\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1660}, {\"ngram\": \"Mizutori\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That means the key over the remaining weeks might be to simply polish their routines and minimize any mistakes.\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the key\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1752}, {\"ngram\": \"the remaining weeks\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1777}, {\"ngram\": \"their routines\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1818}, {\"ngram\": \"any mistakes\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was quite a surprise, since China had long had a higher D-score than Japan,\\\" said Kazuma Kaya, who won bronze in the pommel horse in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1992, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1881, \"end\": 1886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9381970247967566, \"rank\": 0.06192129563232307, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1922, \"end\": 1927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 3.76747469383612e-13, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 1935, \"end\": 1946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazuma_Kaya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kazuma Kaya\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazuma_Kaya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazuma_Kaya\"}, {\"begin\": 1986, \"end\": 1991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4937983910032014e-18, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"quite a surprise\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"a higher D-score\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1916}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 1962}, {\"ngram\": \"the pommel horse\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 1982}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In that sense, we have the strongest five members this time.\\\"\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2055, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that sense\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2007}, {\"ngram\": \"the strongest five members\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Led by Hashimoto, Japan took the title at the World Championships last October with a total score of 255.594 points \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 nearly two points ahead of China \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 although the runners-up competed without their ace all-arounder Zhang Boheng.\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2075, \"end\": 2080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 3.76747469383612e-13, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 2204, \"end\": 2209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9381970247967566, \"rank\": 0.06192129563232307, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2278, \"end\": 2290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Boheng\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zhang Boheng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Boheng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Boheng\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hashimoto\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2073}, {\"ngram\": \"the title\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2095}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Championships\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2122}, {\"ngram\": \"a total score\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2154}, {\"ngram\": \"255.594 points\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2172}, {\"ngram\": \"the runners\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2234}, {\"ngram\": \"their ace\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the 24-year-old Zhang added to the Olympic roster this time, China will be a formidable force, Mizutori warned, leaving Japan little room for error.\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2359, \"end\": 2364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9381970247967566, \"rank\": 0.06192129563232307, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2418, \"end\": 2423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 3.76747469383612e-13, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 24-year-old Zhang\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2319}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic roster\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2347}, {\"ngram\": \"a formidable force\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2391}, {\"ngram\": \"Mizutori\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2401}, {\"ngram\": \"little room\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2435}, {\"ngram\": \"error\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zhang is also set to give Hashimoto a run for his money, with the latter still nursing a finger injury that he said put him at 60 percent at last week's training session.\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2474, \"end\": 2483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.554729998596519e-58, \"text\": \"Hashimoto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Zhang\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2453},